b:["$","p",null,{"style":"$a:props:style","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Humidity (70–90% in summer):"}]," Sustained moisture breeds mold, mildew, and rot in wood. Even sealed wood eventually absorbs moisture through end cuts and fastener holes. Composite's plastic cap prevents penetration."]}]
c:["$","p",null,{"style":"$a:props:style","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"UV exposure (200+ sunny days/year):"}]," Bleaches wood to gray within 12 months. Stain helps but must be reapplied every 1–2 years. Composite uses UV-stabilized pigments that fade minimally and stabilize."]}]
d:["$","p",null,{"style":"$a:props:style","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Insect damage:"}]," Carpenter bees, termites, and wood-boring beetles target untreated wood in Virginia. Composite has no organic food source for insects."]}]
